                     <title type="complete">Copy of the epitaph of <ref type="pers" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9286Tasfase">Tasfā Ṣǝyon</ref></title>
                     <note>According to 
                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RJFA2TG3"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Bausi1989MssBNCF"/><title level="a">I manoscritti etiopici di J.M. Wansleben nella Biblioteca Nazionale Centrale di Firenze</title><title level="j">Rassegna di Studi Etiopici</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Alessandro</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Bausi</t:surname></author><date>1991</date><biblScope unit="volume">33 (1989)</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">5-33</biblScope><note type="url">http://www.jstor.org/stable/41292808</note><citedRange unit="page">20</citedRange></bibl>,
                        the epitaph was copied when <ref type="pers" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10036Wansleb">Johann-Michael Wansleben</ref> visited 
                        <ref type="ins" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0302SanStefano">Santo Stefano de' Mori</ref> in <date from="1665" to="1666">1665–1666</date>.
                     </note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        Tesfazionis Abissini epitaphium, quod est Romae in templo<lb/>
                        S. Stefani, post S. Petri templum.<lb/>
                        ዝየ፡ ተቀብረ፡ ተስፋ፡ ጺዮን፡ ኢትዮጵያዊ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ዝክርዎ፡ ለጸሎትክሙ፡<lb/>
                        ወመሥዋዕክሙ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በእንተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወበእንተ፡ እሙ፡ ለኢየሱስ፡ አሜን፡<lb/>
                        Tesfa Zion Malbazo eremita etiops, cognomento Petrus <gap reason="ellipsis"/><lb/>
                        አዕረፈ፡ አመ፡ ፲፰፡ ለነሐሲ፡ በ፡ ፲፭፻፶፭፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡<lb/>
                        Aliud Aethiopis epitaphium quod in eodem templo videtur.<lb/>
                        ናሁ፡ ናዜክር፡ ንሕነ፡ አባ፡ ሀብተ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘደብረ፡ ጉባኤ፡ ወአባ፡ ተክለ፡ ሀይማ<lb/>ኖት፡ 
                        ዘደብረ፡ ዲማ፡ ነጋድያን፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><lb/>
                        Aliud Aethiopis Epitaphium ibi videtur h.ni.<lb/>
                        Hic jacet pater frater Marcus Aethiops, prior huius loci,<lb/>
                        qui obiit 13 januarii 1582
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  
